Everyone wants to go back again before we leave. Sit upstairs. Enjoy!

How is this reasonable prices ? The $17 falafel platter is actually six pieces of falafel, a sauce-sized cup of hummus, and a tiny "salad" of two tomatoes, a few shredded pieces of lettuce and a singular olive. Is a platter not in its very nature meant to indicate a large dish meant for sharing? Considering the abundance of other falafel joints nearby, you'd be better off at any of them where the portions are larger and the prices more affordable. You can get a whole pita bowl at yafa's for half the price and walk away with leftovers.

I have been eating there for years, and enjoy the traditional greek fare; Gyro's, souvlaki, spanakopita, and their specials. parking is challenging, but the metro and the bus stops are nearby.  Handicapped access is challenging because the restaurant is a converted row house, and has some steps.  It is a serve yourself kind of a place, where you order and bring a tray of food to your table ; bear this in mind if you go there, but I feel it is worth it to get a good greek meal. You can always eat outside in nice weather,  and the bustle of the Dupont circle area has a great energy. Zorba's is friendly, affordable, and a great place to dine.

Zorba's is a true DC gem!  Family owned and located just off the Dupont Circle Metro (North side) exit for more than 34 years, Zorba's has something delicious on its menu for everyone. Great for kids, families, and couples alike. Food is authentic and prepared hot and fresh. It's a little old-school (you order at the counter and pick up your food when your buzzer rings), but that helps keep costs lower -- and who doesn't like that?!  Try the souvlaki platter or Aegean salad with pork kabobs. The mousakka is also excellent, as are their pizzas (the Greeks made them first!). For the latter, my preference is the Santorini. The customer service is also outstanding. Saul, who's most regularly behind the counter in the evenings, will make sure you have an excellent experience. And don't forget to save room for dessert -- the baklava is not to be missed!
The wine is fantastic!!!
